    "summary": "I worked in Hungary for 23 years in the education system from elementary schools to high schools as a history teacher. I have experience to work with Microsoft Office, used the MS Publisher regularly to create the school newspaper and I can learn to use new technology fast. I am familiar with different IT hardwares and softwares and also can use the social media. I am good in making a presentation (with Power Point or Prezi.com) and I also want to learn about the newest technologies. \nAs a high school teacher I organised many short and long term projects with my students on tolerance, racism and other sensitive topics. I have working history with Hungarian and international organisations too (e.g. Haver Alapitvany \u2013 www.haver.hu, Wallenberg Egyesulet - www.wallenbergegyesulet.hu, Certopa Foundation \u2013 www.cenrtopa.org, Facing History and Ourselves -  www.facinghistory.org).\n\nPersonal interests: reading, learning, swimming, walking, travel, gardening, opera and jazz.\n\nhttp://partnershipassociation.wordpress.com/2010/10/17/usa-day-in-mezobereny/\n\nhttp://www.centropa.org/hu/teaching-materials/oravazlat-katarina-lofflerova\n\nhttp://www.centropa.org/hu/teaching-materials/szemleletformalas-es-kozos-munka-centropa-filmjeinek-segitsegevel\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=87UMPvHwmM4",
